  "tutorPrompt": "Topic: Patterns & Sequences\nLearning objective: By the end of this lesson Romy will continue number and shape patterns, state the rule of a sequence, fill missing terms and spot the odd one out.\nIsland: cherry_blossom_island\nDifficulty: 4 out of 10\nMechanics for stages 1-8 (use exactly these, in any order): pattern_input, drag_sort, fill_blank, multi_choice, true_false, corridor_choice, match_pairs, find_unknown\nStage 9: boss_mix\nKey concepts to cover: continuing patterns, finding the rule, missing terms, odd one out, skip-counting\nContext: Patterns are one of Romy's strengths, so the plan opens here to build confidence before the harder fractions block. It also quietly rehearses skip-counting (2s, 5s, 10s), the backbone she will lean on for fractions and times.\nChild weak points: Fractions (meaning and comparison), telling time on analogue clocks, money and change\nTutor note: Watch whether Romy names the rule aloud before answering. If she only guesses the next term without stating '+3' or '×2', slow down on find_unknown rounds.",
